'''Katakurabe no Mikoto''' (片倉辺命) is a deity from the folk tradition of the {{ill|Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|12=draft}} in Nagano Prefecture, associated with the {{ill|Suwa faith|ja|諏訪信仰|12=draft}}.
[[File:Suwa-taisha Kamisha Maemiya - Wakamiko-sha (若御子社).jpg|thumb|250px|Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya]]
== Overview == Katakurabe no Mikoto is also written as '''片倉辺神''' or '''片倉辺尊'''. A related deity with a similar name, '''Mikurabe no Mikoto''' (御倉辺命), is mentioned, though it is unclear if they are the same deity.
Katakurabe no Mikoto is considered a child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|12=draft}}, residing at the southern foot of Mount Moriya (片倉) and believed to be enshrined in the former {{ill|Nyukatakura Village|ja|入片倉村|12=draft}} of the Saku District. The deity's burial site is said to be in the Saku District.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1921|p=17}}
According to the genealogical record of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|12=draft}}, written in the early Meiji period, Katakurabe no Mikoto's son, {{ill|Kodamahiko no Mikoto|ja|児玉彦命|12=draft}}, succeeded {{ill|Chikatsugami|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|12=draft}} as the fourth-generation leader. The ''Suwa Clan Genealogy: Continued Volume'' identifies Katakurabe no Mikoto as the ancestral deity of the {{ill|Katakura clan|ja|片倉氏|12=draft}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|thumb|center|170px|Genealogy of the first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|12=draft}}]]
