'''Katakurabe no Mikoto''' (片倉辺命) is a deity from the folk tradition of the {{ill|Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Nagano Prefecture, associated with the {{ill|Suwa faith|ja|諏訪信仰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

[[File:Suwa-taisha Kamisha Maemiya - Wakamiko-sha (若御子社).jpg|thumb|250px|Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya]]

== Overview ==
Katakurabe no Mikoto is also written as '''片倉辺神''' or '''片倉辺尊'''. A related deity with a similar name, '''Mikurabe no Mikoto''' (御倉辺命), is mentioned, though it is unclear if they are the same deity.

Katakurabe no Mikoto is considered a child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, residing at the southern foot of Mount Moriya (片倉) and believed to be enshrined in the former {{ill|Nyukatakura Village|ja|入片倉村|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} of the Saku District. The deity's burial site is said to be in the Saku District.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1921|p=17}}

According to the genealogical record of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, written in the early Meiji period, Katakurabe no Mikoto's son, {{ill|Kodamahiko no Mikoto|ja|児玉彦命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, succeeded {{ill|Chikatsugami|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} as the fourth-generation leader. The ''Suwa Clan Genealogy: Continued Volume'' identifies Katakurabe no Mikoto as the ancestral deity of the {{ill|Katakura clan|ja|片倉氏|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|thumb|center|170px|Genealogy of the first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}]]

Katakurabe no Mikoto is the child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Yasakatome no Kami|ja|八坂刀売神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. While the consort is unknown, Katakurabe no Mikoto is said to have three children: {{ill|Kodamahiko no Mikoto|ja|児玉彦命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kamitsumitama no Kami|ja|上津御玉神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Shimotsumitama no Kami|ja|下津御玉神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1921|pp=17–18}}

Among them, Kodamahiko no Mikoto succeeded {{ill|Chikatsugami|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in both religious and political roles, married {{ill|Mitsutamahime no Kami|ja|美都多麻比売神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, daughter of {{ill|Moritatsugami|ja|守達神|1=Moritachi no Kami|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and fathered {{ill|Yakushigami|ja|八櫛神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. For this reason, Kodamahiko no Mikoto is counted as the fourth generation in the genealogical records of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Shrines Dedicated to Katakurabe no Mikoto ==
* {{ill|Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya|ja|諏訪大社上社前宮若御子社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Miyagawa, Chino City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Jūgoshajinja (Chino City)|ja|十五社神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Toyohira, Chino City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Akimiya|ja|諏訪大社下社秋宮若宮社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Shimosuwa Town, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Harumiya|ja|諏訪大社下社春宮若宮社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Shimosuwa Town, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Jūgoshajinja (Okaya City)|ja|十五社神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Honcho, Okaya City, Nagano Prefecture)

