'''Katakurabe no Mikoto''' (片倉辺命) is a deity from the folk tradition of the {{ill|Suwa Region|lt=Suwa Region|lt=Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa region|qq=}} in Nagano Prefecture, associated with the {{ill|Suwa Shrine|lt=Suwa Shrine|lt=Suwa faith|ja|諏訪信仰|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa faith|qq=}}.

[[File:Suwa-taisha Kamisha Maemiya - Wakamiko-sha (若御子社).jpg|thumb|250px|Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya]]

== Overview ==
Katakurabe no Mikoto is also written as '''片倉辺神''' or '''片倉辺尊'''. A related deity with a similar name, '''Mikurabe no Mikoto''' (御倉辺命), is mentioned, though it is unclear if they are the same deity.

Katakurabe no Mikoto is considered a child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata no Kami|qq=}}, residing at the southern foot of Mount Moriya (片倉) and believed to be enshrined in the former {{ill|Nyukatakura Village|ja|入片倉村|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nyukatakura Village|qq=}} of the Saku District. The deity's burial site is said to be in the Saku District.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1921|p=17}}

According to the genealogical record of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}}, written in the early Meiji period, Katakurabe no Mikoto's son, {{ill|Kodamahiko-no-Mikoto|ja|児玉彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kodamahiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, succeeded {{ill|Chikatsugami|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatsugami|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=}} as the fourth-generation leader. The ''Suwa Clan Genealogy: Continued Volume'' identifies Katakurabe no Mikoto as the ancestral deity of the {{ill|Katakura clan|ja|片倉氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katakura clan|qq=}}.

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|thumb|center|170px|Genealogy of the first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}}]]

Katakurabe no Mikoto is the child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata no Kami|qq=}} and {{ill|Yasakatome no Kami|ja|八坂刀売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasakatome no Kami|qq=}}. While the consort is unknown, Katakurabe no Mikoto is said to have three children: {{ill|Kodamahiko-no-Mikoto|ja|児玉彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kodamahiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Kamitsumitama no Kami|ja|上津御玉神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsumitama no Kami|qq=}}, and {{ill|Shimotsumitama no Kami|ja|下津御玉神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimotsumitama no Kami|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1921|pp=17–18}}

Among them, Kodamahiko no Mikoto succeeded {{ill|Chikatsugami|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatsugami|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=}} in both religious and political roles, married {{ill|Mitsutamahime no Kami|ja|美都多麻比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsutamahime no Kami|qq=}}, daughter of {{ill|Moritatsugami|ja|守達神|1=Moritachi no Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritatsugami|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritachi no Kami|qq=}}, and fathered {{ill|Yakushigami|ja|八櫛神|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushigami|qq=}}. For this reason, Kodamahiko no Mikoto is counted as the fourth generation in the genealogical records of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}}.

== Shrines Dedicated to Katakurabe no Mikoto ==
* {{ill|Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya|ja|諏訪大社上社前宮若御子社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiko-sha at Suwa Taisha Kamisha Maemiya|qq=}} (Miyagawa, Chino City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Jūgosha Shrine (Okaya City)|ja|十五社神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jūgoshajinja (Chino City)|qq=}} (Toyohira, Chino City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Akimiya|ja|諏訪大社下社秋宮若宮社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Akimiya|qq=}} (Shimosuwa Town, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Harumiya|ja|諏訪大社下社春宮若宮社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya-sha at Suwa Taisha Shimosha Harumiya|qq=}} (Shimosuwa Town, Nagano Prefecture)
